command.framework

Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • command.framework.Command
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CmdDateTime, CmdExit, CmdFormat, CmdHelp, CmdRename, CmdType, CmdVer

    public abstract class Command
extends Object
    Abstract class for all commands.
    Command-Pattern: Command.

    Responsibilities:
    • declares an interface for executing an operation. This is
      - execute()
    • declares an in interface to pass parameters controlling the execution. This is
      - checkNumberOfParameters()
      - checkParameterValues()
    • provides the concrete command with various information. This is
      - getDrive()
      - getParameters()
    • provides functionality to the invoker. This is
      - compareCmdName()
      - setParameters()
      - checkParameters()
      - reset()
    Note: checkParameters() is a Template Method and checkNumberOfParameters() and checkParameterValues() are the hooks for deriving classes

      • checkParameters

        public final boolean checkParameters(Outputter outputter)
                              throws Exception
        Checks the passed parameters. This consists of three steps which are both overrideable by concrete commands.
        1.) Check the number of parameters.
        2.) Check the values of all passed parameters
        3.) Assign the parameters to attributes in the concrete commands.

        Template Method Pattern: Template Method.
        Parameters:
        outputter - The outputter must be used to output any error description.
        Returns:
        • true if number and values of the parameters are correct. Execute() may use the parameters afterwards unchecked.
        • false if the number is below or above excepted range or if any value is incorrect. An explaining error message must be given by the concrete command.
        Throws:
        Exception - Thrown if this.parameters is not set.

      • checkNumberOfParameters

        protected boolean checkNumberOfParameters(int number)
        Can be overwritten by the concrete commands if something must be checked. Checks if the number of parameters is in range. Do not output anything, an explaining error message is output by the abstract command.

        Template Method Pattern: Hook.
        Parameters:
        number - Number of parameters passed by the caller.
        Returns:
        • true if number of parameters is within expected range
        • false otherwise

      • checkParameterValues

        protected boolean checkParameterValues(Outputter outputter)
        Can be overwritten by the concrete commands if at least the value of one parameter must be checked. Checks all values of all passed parameters. An explaining error message must be output by the concrete command.

        Template Method Pattern: Hook.
        Parameters:
        outputter - The outputter must be used to output error messages.
        Returns:
        • true if all values of all parameters passed are correct.
        • false if at least one value of one parameter in incorrect.

      • setParameters

        protected void setParameters()
        Can be overwritten by the concrete commands if the list of parameters is very complex. Assign the parameters in the parameter-list to appropriate attributes in the concrete commands.

      • execute

        public abstract void execute(Outputter outputter)
        Must be overwritten by the concrete commands to implement the execution of the command.
        Parameters:
        outputter - Must be used to output any text.
